## Task
Create the shared ESLint configuration for the monorepo.

## File to Create
templates/packages/config/eslint-config-custom.cjs

## Configuration
```javascript
module.exports = {
  root: true,
  env: {
    browser: true,
    es2022: true,
    node: true,
  },
  extends: [
    'eslint:recommended',
  ],
  parserOptions: {
    ecmaVersion: 'latest',
    sourceType: 'module',
  },
  rules: {
    'no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],
    'no-console': 'warn',
  },
  overrides: [
    {
      files: ['*.ts', '*.tsx'],
      parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',
      extends: [
        'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended',
      ],
      rules: {
        '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],
        '@typescript-eslint/explicit-function-return-type': 'off',
      },
    },
    {
      files: ['*.tsx'],
      extends: [
        'plugin:react/recommended',
        'plugin:react-hooks/recommended',
      ],
      settings: {
        react: { version: 'detect' },
      },
      rules: {
        'react/react-in-jsx-scope': 'off',
      },
    },
  ],
};
```

## Usage in Apps
```javascript
// apps/web/.eslintrc.cjs
module.exports = {
  extends: ['@{{scope}}/config/eslint-config-custom'],
};
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Config exports correctly as CJS
- [ ] Works with TypeScript files
- [ ] Works with React/JSX files
- [ ] Apps can extend this config

## Task
Implement the template variable replacement engine that transforms {{variable}} tokens.

## Supported Variables
```typescript
interface TemplateVariables {
  projectName: string;    // {{projectName}} -> "my-project"
  scope: string;          // {{scope}} -> "@my-project"
  year: string;           // {{year}} -> "2024"
  // Package versions from defaults
  reactVersion: string;
  typescriptVersion: string;
  // etc.
}
```

## API Design
```typescript
// Replace all {{variable}} patterns in content
function applyVariables(
  content: string, 
  variables: TemplateVariables
): string;

// Build variables object from config
function buildVariables(config: ProjectConfig): TemplateVariables;
```

## Implementation Notes
- Use regex: /\{\{(\w+)\}\}/g
- Throw error for undefined variables
- Handle nested JSON (don't break JSON syntax)
- Consider escaping for special chars

## File Location
src/generator/applyVariables.ts

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All {{variable}} patterns replaced
- [ ] Undefined variables throw helpful error
- [ ] Works with JSON files (valid after replacement)
- [ ] Handles edge cases (empty string, special chars)

## Task
Create a logger utility that respects --verbose flag and provides consistent output formatting.

## API Design
```typescript
interface Logger {
  info(message: string): void;
  success(message: string): void;
  warn(message: string): void;
  error(message: string): void;
  debug(message: string): void;  // only shows with --verbose

  // Progress helpers
  step(current: number, total: number, message: string): void;

  // Formatting
  dim(message: string): string;
  bold(message: string): string;
}

function createLogger(verbose: boolean): Logger;
```

## Implementation Notes
- Use ANSI color codes for terminal output
- debug() should no-op when verbose=false
- Consider using chalk or picocolors (or raw ANSI)
- step() format: "[1/5] Installing dependencies..."

